Look.  We don't ship after every changelist.  So marking a defect fixed means that you can *EXPECT* the issue to be resolved in the next released build.  So the issue is fixed, and can be validated upon the next release.

Because that just not how any defect tracking system that I have ever used works. 
Basic status are: 
Proposed - defect is submitted for review
InWork/Active - defect is reviewed and is in-work to either dev for fix or QA for additional info
Fixed - defect has been fixed by dev to be verified in the next build.
Verified - defect has been verified by QA and can be closed put on regression list.
Closed - defect is completely handled.
